Police in Democratic of Congo’s Capital Use Tear Gas to Break Up Protest

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-09-01T14:25:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/police-in-democratic-of-congo-s-capital-use-tear-gas-to-break-up-protest.html
Police fired shots and tear gas to
disperse an opposition protest in  Democratic Republic  of Congo’s
capital, Kinshasa, according to Serge Mayamba, the chief of
staff of the opposition Union for Democracy and Social Progress.  The UDSP is calling for greater transparency in general
elections planned for later this year, Mayamba said in a phone
interview from the city today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
